name: isSnooperEnabled
desc: Returns whether snooping is enabled or not.

name: canCommandSenderUseCommand
desc: Returns true if the command sender is allowed to use the given command.

name: translateString
desc: Translates and formats the given string key with the given arguments.

name: getCommandSenderName
desc: Gets the name of this command sender (usually username, but possibly "Rcon")

name: resetLog
desc: Clears the RCon log

name: getDistance
desc: Gets the distance to the position. Args: x, y, z

name: setLocationAndAngles
desc: Sets the location and Yaw/Pitch of an entity in the world

name: getBrightness
desc: Gets how bright this entity is.

name: writeEntityToNBT
desc: (abstract) Protected helper method to write subclass entity data to NBT.

name: setFire
desc: Sets entity to burn for x amount of seconds, cannot lower amount of existing fire.

name: setVelocity
desc: Sets the velocity to the args. Args: x, y, z

name: doBlockCollisions
desc: Checks for block collisions, and calls the associated onBlockCollided method for the collided block.

name: setBeenAttacked
desc: Sets that this entity has been attacked.

name: readFromNBT
desc: Reads the entity from NBT (calls an abstract helper method to read specialized data)

name: getParts
desc: Return the Entity parts making up this Entity (currently only for dragons)

name: getEntityString
desc: Returns the string that identifies this Entity's class

name: getEntityName
desc: Gets the username of the entity.

name: addVelocity
desc: Adds to the current velocity of the entity. Args: x, y, z

name: dropItem
desc: Drops an item stack at the entity's position. Args: itemID, count

name: isWet
desc: Checks if this entity is either in water or on an open air block in rain (used in wolves).

name: isBurning
desc: Returns true if the entity is on fire. Used by render to add the fire effect on rendering.

name: isEntityEqual
desc: Returns true if Entity argument is equal to this Entity

name: setWorld
desc: Sets the reference to the World object.

name: onEntityUpdate
desc: Gets called every tick from main Entity class

name: setSprinting
desc: Set sprinting switch for Entity.

name: getDistanceToEntity
desc: Returns the distance to the entity. Args: entity

name: getYOffset
desc: Returns the Y Offset of this entity.

name: setHeadRotationYaw
desc: Sets the head's yaw rotation of the entity.

name: playStepSound
desc: Plays step sound at given x, y, z for the entity

name: readEntityFromNBT
desc: (abstract) Protected helper method to read subclass entity data from NBT.

name: isOffsetPositionInLiquid
desc: Checks if the offset position from the entity's current position is inside of liquid. Args: x, y, z

name: addEntityID
desc: adds the ID of this entity to the NBT given

name: getLookVec
desc: returns a (normalized) vector of where this entity is looking

name: canTriggerWalking
desc: returns if this entity triggers Block.onEntityWalking on the blocks they walk on. used for spiders and wolves to prevent them from trampling crops

name: getMountedYOffset
desc: Returns the Y offset from the entity's position for any entity riding this one.

name: setOnFireFromLava
desc: Called whenever the entity is walking inside of lava.

name: getBoundingBox
desc: returns the bounding box for this entity

name: pushOutOfBlocks
desc: Adds velocity to push the entity out of blocks at the specified x, y, z position Args: x, y, z

name: newFloatNBTList
desc: Returns a new NBTTagList filled with the specified floats

name: isSprinting
desc: Get if the Entity is sprinting.

name: setFlag
desc: Enable or disable a entity flag, see getEntityFlag to read the know flags.

name: dropItemWithOffset
desc: Drops an item stack with a specified y offset. Args: itemID, count, yOffset

name: isInsideOfMaterial
desc: Checks if the current block the entity is within of the specified material type

name: setPositionAndRotation2
desc: Sets the position and rotation. Only difference from the other one is no bounding on the rotation. Args: posX, posY, posZ, yaw, pitch

name: performHurtAnimation
desc: Setups the entity to do the hurt animation. Only used by packets in multiplayer.

name: handleLavaMovement
desc: Whether or not the current entity is in lava

name: moveFlying
desc: Used in both water and by flying objects

name: unmountEntity
desc: Called when a player unounts an entity.

name: setCurrentItemOrArmor
desc: Sets the held item, or an armor slot. Slot 0 is held item. Slot 1-4 is armor. Params: Item, slot

name: setInPortal
desc: Called by portal blocks when an entity is within it.

name: updateFallState
desc: Takes in the distance the entity has fallen this tick and whether its on the ground to update the fall distance and deal fall damage if landing on the ground.  Args: distanceFallenThisTick, onGround

name: preparePlayerToSpawn
desc: Keeps moving the entity up so it isn't colliding with blocks and other requirements for this entity to be spawned (only actually used on players though its also on Entity)

name: extinguish
desc: Removes fire from entity.

name: canBeCollidedWith
desc: Returns true if other Entities should be prevented from moving through this Entity.

name: getDistanceSqToEntity
desc: Returns the squared distance to the entity. Args: entity

name: fall
desc: Called when the mob is falling. Calculates and applies fall damage.

name: onUpdate
desc: Called to update the entity's position/logic.

name: handleWaterMovement
desc: Returns if this entity is in water and will end up adding the waters velocity to the entity

name: getTexture
desc: Returns the texture's file path as a String.

name: onKillEntity
desc: This method gets called when the entity kills another one.

name: canAttackWithItem
desc: If returns false, the item will not inflict any damage against entities.

name: kill
desc: sets the dead flag. Used when you fall off the bottom of the world.

name: onStruckByLightning
desc: Called when a lightning bolt hits the entity.

name: mountEntity
desc: Called when a player mounts an entity. e.g. mounts a pig, mounts a boat.

name: setPositionAndRotation
desc: Sets the entity's position and rotation. Args: posX, posY, posZ, yaw, pitch

name: dealFireDamage
desc: Will deal the specified amount of damage to the entity if the entity isn't immune to fire damage. Args: amountDamage

name: setAngles
desc: Adds par1*0.15 to the entity's yaw, and *subtracts* par2*0.15 from the pitch. Clamps pitch from -90 to 90. Both arguments in degrees.

name: getFlag
desc: Returns true if the flag is active for the entity. Known flags: 0) is burning; 1) is sneaking; 2) is riding something; 3) is sprinting; 4) is eating

name: addToPlayerScore
desc: Adds a value to the player score. Currently not actually used and the entity passed in does nothing. Args: entity, scoreToAdd

name: interact
desc: Called when a player interacts with a mob. e.g. gets milk from a cow, gets into the saddle on a pig.

name: newDoubleNBTList
desc: creates a NBT list from the array of doubles passed to this function

name: isEntityAlive
desc: Checks whether target entity is alive.

name: isInWater
desc: Checks if this entity is inside water (if inWater field is true as a result of handleWaterMovement() returning true)

name: moveEntity
desc: Tries to moves the entity by the passed in displacement. Args: x, y, z

name: getDistanceSq
desc: Gets the squared distance to the position. Args: x, y, z

name: isSneaking
desc: Returns if this entity is sneaking.

name: isEntityInsideOpaqueBlock
desc: Checks if this entity is inside of an opaque block

name: setSneaking
desc: Sets the sneaking flag.

name: attackEntityFrom
desc: Called when the entity is attacked.

name: updateRidden
desc: Handles updating while being ridden by an entity

name: entityDropItem
desc: Drops an item at the position of the entity.

name: onCollideWithPlayer
desc: Called by a player entity when they collide with an entity

name: setRotation
desc: Sets the rotation of the entity

name: isInRangeToRenderVec3D
desc: Checks using a Vec3d to determine if this entity is within range of that vector to be rendered. Args: vec3D

name: canBePushed
desc: Returns true if this entity should push and be pushed by other entities when colliding.

name: setSize
desc: Sets the width and height of the entity. Args: width, height

name: setDead
desc: Will get destroyed next tick.

name: setPosition
desc: Sets the x,y,z of the entity from the given parameters. Also seems to set up a bounding box.

name: applyEntityCollision
desc: Applies a velocity to each of the entities pushing them away from each other. Args: entity

name: writeToNBT
desc: Save the entity to NBT (calls an abstract helper method to write extra data)

name: setInWeb
desc: Sets the Entity inside a web block.

name: isInRangeToRenderDist
desc: Checks if the entity is in range to render by using the past in distance and comparing it to its average edge length * 64 * renderDistanceWeight Args: distance

name: getCollisionBox
desc: Returns a boundingBox used to collide the entity with other entities and blocks. This enables the entity to be pushable on contact, like boats or minecarts.

name: isRiding
desc: Returns true if the entity is riding another entity, used by render to rotate the legs to be in 'sit' position for players.

name: onImpact
desc: Called when this EntityThrowable hits a block or entity.

name: getGravityVelocity
desc: Gets the amount of gravity to apply to the thrown entity with each tick.

name: setThrowableHeading
desc: Similar to setArrowHeading, it's point the throwable entity to a x, y, z direction.

name: getPotionDamage
desc: Returns the damage value of the thrown potion that this EntityPotion represents.

name: moveTowards
desc: The location the eye should float/move towards. Currently used for moving towards the nearest stronghold. Args: strongholdX, strongholdY, strongholdZ

name: onImpact
desc: Called when this EntityFireball hits a block or entity.

name: setKnockbackStrength
desc: Sets the amount of knockback the arrow applies when it hits a mob.

name: getIsCritical
desc: Whether the arrow has a stream of critical hit particles flying behind it.

name: setIsCritical
desc: Whether the arrow has a stream of critical hit particles flying behind it.

name: setTimeSinceHit
desc: Sets the time to count down from since the last time entity was hit.

name: setDamageTaken
desc: Sets the damage taken from the last hit.

name: getForwardDirection
desc: Gets the forward direction of the entity.

name: getTimeSinceHit
desc: Gets the time since the last hit.

name: setForwardDirection
desc: Sets the forward direction of the entity.

name: getDamageTaken
desc: Gets the damage taken from the last hit.

name: combineItems
desc: Tries to merge this item with the item passed as the parameter. Returns true if successful. Either this item or the other item will  be removed from the world.

name: onInventoryChanged
desc: Called when an the contents of an Inventory change, usually

name: getInventoryStackLimit
desc: Returns the maximum stack size for a inventory slot. Seems to always be 64, possibly will be extended. *Isn't this more of a set than a get?*

name: decrStackSize
desc: Removes from an inventory slot (first arg) up to a specified number (second arg) of items and returns them in a new stack.

name: setInventorySlotContents
desc: Sets the given item stack to the specified slot in the inventory (can be crafting or armor sections).

name: isUseableByPlayer
desc: Do not make give this method the name canInteractWith because it clashes with Container

name: getStackInSlot
desc: Returns the stack in slot i

name: getSizeInventory
desc: Returns the number of slots in the inventory.

name: getInvName
desc: Returns the name of the inventory.

name: getStackInSlotOnClosing
desc: When some containers are closed they call this on each slot, then drop whatever it returns as an EntityItem - like when you close a workbench GUI.

name: addMapping
desc: Adds a new two-way mapping between the class and its string name in both hashmaps.

name: readFromNBT
desc: Reads a tile entity from NBT.

name: setWorldObj
desc: Sets the worldObj for this tileEntity.

name: writeToNBT
desc: Writes a tile entity to NBT.

name: getBlockType
desc: Gets the block type at the location of this entity (client-only).

name: validate
desc: validates a tile entity

name: invalidate
desc: invalidates a tile entity

name: getWorldObj
desc: Returns the worldObj for this tileEntity.

name: receiveClientEvent
desc: Called when a client event is received with the event number and argument, see World.sendClientEvent

name: updateEntity
desc: Allows the entity to update its state. Overridden in most subclasses, e.g. the mob spawner uses this to count ticks and creates a new spawn inside its implementation.

name: createAndLoadEntity
desc: Creates a new entity and loads its data from the specified NBT.

name: getDistanceFrom
desc: Returns the square of the distance between this entity and the passed in coordinates.

name: getDescriptionPacket
desc: Overriden in a sign to provide the text.

name: isInvalid
desc: returns true if tile entity is invalid, false otherwise

name: updateContainingBlockInfo
desc: Causes the TileEntity to reset all it's cached values for it's container block, blockID, metaData and in the case of chests, the adjcacent chest check

name: getBlockMetadata
desc: Returns block data at the location of this entity (client-only).

name: getProgress
desc: Get interpolated progress value (between lastProgress and progress) given the fractional time between ticks as an argument.

name: getPistonOrientation
desc: Returns the orientation of the piston as an int

name: clearPistonTileEntity
desc: removes a pistons tile entity (and if the piston is moving, stops it)

name: isExtending
desc: Returns true if a piston is extending

name: getFilledSlots
desc: returns an integer with each bit specifying wether that slot of the stand contains a potion

name: getPotionResult
desc: The result of brewing a potion of the specified damage value with an ingredient itemstack.

name: addItem
desc: Add item stack in first available inventory slot

name: getMobEntity
desc: will create the entity from the internalID the first time it is accessed

name: anyPlayerInRange
desc: Returns true if there is a player in range (using World.getClosestPlayer)

name: updateDelay
desc: Sets the delay before a new spawn (base delay of 200 + random number up to 600).

name: getCookProgressScaled
desc: Returns an integer between 0 and the passed value representing how close the current item is to being completely cooked

name: getItemBurnTime
desc: Returns the number of ticks that the supplied fuel item will keep the furnace burning, or 0 if the item isn't fuel

name: smeltItem
desc: Turn one item from the furnace source stack into the appropriate smelted item in the furnace result stack

name: isBurning
desc: Returns true if the furnace is currently burning

name: isItemFuel
desc: Return true if item is a fuel source (getItemBurnTime() > 0).

name: canSmelt
desc: Returns true if the furnace can smelt an item, i.e. has a source item, destination stack isn't full, etc.

name: getBurnTimeRemainingScaled
desc: Returns an integer between 0 and the passed value representing how much burn time is left on the current fuel item, where 0 means that the item is exhausted and the passed value means that the item is fresh

name: setEditable
desc: Sets the sign's isEditable flag to the specified parameter.

name: changePitch
desc: change pitch by -> (currentPitch + 1) % 25

name: triggerNote
desc: plays the stored note

name: checkForAdjacentChests
desc: Performs the check for adjacent chests to determine if this chest is double or not.

name: decrementAnimations
desc: Decrement the number of animations remaining. Only called on client side. This is used to handle the animation of receiving a block.

name: getTotalArmorValue
desc: Based on the damage values and maximum damage values of each armor item, returns the current armor value.

name: hasItemStack
desc: Returns true if the specified ItemStack exists in the inventory.

name: storeItemStack
desc: stores an itemstack in the users inventory

name: setCurrentItem
desc: Sets a specific itemID as the current item being held (only if it exists on the hotbar)

name: consumeInventoryItem
desc: removed one item of specified itemID from inventory (if it is in a stack, the stack size will reduce with 1)

name: dropAllItems
desc: Drop all armor and main inventory items.

name: getStrVsBlock
desc: Gets the strength of the current item (tool) against the specified block, 1.0f if not holding anything.

name: armorItemInSlot
desc: returns a player armor item (as itemstack) contained in specified armor slot.

name: addItemStackToInventory
desc: Adds the item stack to the inventory, returns false if it is impossible.

name: writeToNBT
desc: Writes the inventory out as a list of compound tags. This is where the slot indices are used (+100 for armor, +80 for crafting).

name: readFromNBT
desc: Reads from the given tag list and fills the slots in the inventory with the correct items.

name: getDamageVsEntity
desc: Return damage vs an entity done by the current held weapon, or 1 if nothing is held

name: getInventorySlotContainItem
desc: Returns a slot index in main inventory containing a specific itemID

name: getFirstEmptyStack
desc: Returns the first item stack that is empty.

name: getCurrentItem
desc: Returns the item stack currently held by the player.

name: damageArmor
desc: Damages armor in each slot by the specified amount.

name: hasItem
desc: Get if a specifiied item id is inside the inventory.

name: getHotbarSize
desc: Get the size of the player hotbar inventory

name: storePartialItemStack
desc: This function stores as many items of an ItemStack as possible in a matching slot and returns the quantity of left over items.

name: changeCurrentItem
desc: Switch the current item to the next one or the previous one

name: canHarvestBlock
desc: Returns whether the current item (tool) can harvest from the specified block (actually get a result).

name: copyInventory
desc: Copy the ItemStack contents from another InventoryPlayer instance

name: getStackInRowAndColumn
desc: Returns the itemstack in the slot specified (Top left is 0, 0). Args: row, column

name: inventoryResetNeededOnSlotChange
desc: if par1 slot has changed, does resetRecipeAndSlots need to be called?

name: isMinecartPowered
desc: Is this minecart powered (Fuel > 0)

name: getDamage
desc: Gets the current amount of damage the minecart has taken. Decreases over time. The cart breaks when this is over 40.

name: setDamage
desc: Sets the current amount of damage the minecart has taken. Decreases over time. The cart breaks when this is over 40.

name: getRollingDirection
desc: Gets the rolling direction the cart rolls while being attacked. Can be 1 or -1.

name: setRollingDirection
desc: Sets the rolling direction the cart rolls while being attacked. Can be 1 or -1.

name: getRollingAmplitude
desc: Gets the rolling amplitude the cart rolls while being attacked.

name: setRollingAmplitude
desc: Sets the rolling amplitude the cart rolls while being attacked.

name: setMinecartPowered
desc: Set if this minecart is powered (Fuel > 0)

name: onValidSurface
desc: checks to make sure painting can be placed there

name: getXpValue
desc: Returns the XP value of this XP orb.

name: getXPSplit
desc: Get xp split rate (Is called until the xp drop code in EntityLiving.onEntityUpdate is complete)

name: getTextureByXP
desc: Returns a number from 1 to 10 based on how much XP this orb is worth. This is used by RenderXPOrb to determine what texture to use.

name: setParticleTextureIndex
desc: Public method to set private field particleTextureIndex.

name: setBaseSpellTextureIndex
desc: Sets the base spell texture index

name: getSoundVolume
desc: Returns the volume for the sounds this mob makes.

name: getCanSpawnHere
desc: Checks if the entity's current position is a valid location to spawn this entity.

name: getRenderSizeModifier
desc: Returns render size modifier

name: isPlayerSleeping
desc: Returns whether player is sleeping or not

name: onDeathUpdate
desc: handles entity death timer, experience orb and particle creation

name: isMovementBlocked
desc: Dead and sleeping entities cannot move

name: isWithinHomeDistanceCurrentPosition
desc: Returns true if entity is within home distance from current position

name: moveEntityWithHeading
desc: Moves the entity based on the specified heading.  Args: strafe, forward

name: isClientWorld
desc: Returns whether the entity is in a local (client) world

name: rayTrace
desc: Performs a ray trace for the distance specified and using the partial tick time. Args: distance, partialTickTime

name: eatGrassBonus
desc: This function applies the benefits of growing back wool and faster growing up to the acting entity. (This function is used in the AIEatGrass)

name: getSpeedModifier
desc: This method returns a value to be applied directly to entity speed, this factor is less than 1 when a slowdown potion effect is applied, more than 1 when a haste potion effect is applied and 2 for fleeing entities.

name: isOnLadder
desc: returns true if this entity is by a ladder, false otherwise

name: removePotionEffectClient
desc: Remove the speified potion effect from this entity.

name: getItemIcon
desc: Gets the Icon Index of the item currently held

name: getHurtSound
desc: Returns the sound this mob makes when it is hurt.

name: despawnEntity
desc: Makes the entity despawn if requirements are reached

name: setAttackTarget
desc: Sets the active target the Task system uses for tracking

name: faceEntity
desc: Changes pitch and yaw so that the entity calling the function is facing the entity provided as an argument.

name: getTalkInterval
desc: Get number of ticks, at least during which the living entity will be silent.

name: dropFewItems
desc: Drop 0-2 items of this living's type. @param par1 - Whether this entity has recently been hit by a player. @param par2 - Level of Looting used to kill this mob.

name: updateAITick
desc: main AI tick function, replaces updateEntityActionState

name: isChild
desc: If Animal, checks if the age timer is negative

name: getDropItemId
desc: Returns the item ID for the item the mob drops on death.

name: setPositionAndUpdate
desc: Move the entity to the coordinates informed, but keep yaw/pitch values.

name: getEntitySenses
desc: returns the EntitySenses Object for the EntityLiving

name: onLivingUpdate
desc: Called frequently so the entity can update its state every tick as required. For example, zombies and skeletons use this to react to sunlight and start to burn.

name: getAttackTarget
desc: Gets the active target the Task system uses for tracking

name: getLivingSound
desc: Returns the sound this mob makes while it's alive.

name: getMaxSpawnedInChunk
desc: Will return how many at most can spawn in a chunk at once.

name: playLivingSound
desc: Plays living's sound at its position

name: onDeath
desc: Called when the mob's health reaches 0.

name: getVerticalFaceSpeed
desc: The speed it takes to move the entityliving's rotationPitch through the faceEntity method. This is only currently use in wolves.

name: getSoundPitch
desc: Gets the pitch of living sounds in living entities.

name: isAIEnabled
desc: Returns true if the newer Entity AI code should be run

name: knockBack
desc: knocks back this entity

name: applyArmorCalculations
desc: Reduces damage, depending on armor

name: spawnExplosionParticle
desc: Spawns an explosion particle around the Entity's location

name: getTotalArmorValue
desc: Returns the current armor value as determined by a call to InventoryPlayer.getTotalArmorValue

name: setAIMoveSpeed
desc: set the movespeed used for the new AI system

name: getActivePotionEffect
desc: returns the PotionEffect for the supplied Potion if it is active, null otherwise.

name: isEntityUndead
desc: Returns true if this entity is undead.

name: updateRotation
desc: Arguments: current rotation, intended rotation, max increment.

name: jump
desc: Causes this entity to do an upwards motion (jumping).

name: damageEntity
desc: Deals damage to the entity. If its a EntityPlayer then will take damage from the armor first and then health second with the reduced value. Args: damageAmount

name: getPosition
desc: interpolated position vector

name: getCreatureAttribute
desc: Get this Entity's EnumCreatureAttribute

name: renderBrokenItemStack
desc: Renders broken item particles using the given ItemStack

name: applyPotionDamageCalculations
desc: Reduces damage, depending on potions

name: getDeathSound
desc: Returns the sound this mob makes on death.

name: getLook
desc: interpolated look vector

name: getSwingProgress
desc: Returns where in the swing animation the living entity is (from 0 to 1).  Args: partialTickTime

name: decreaseAirSupply
desc: Decrements the entity's air supply when underwater

name: isPlayer
desc: Only use is to identify if class is an instance of player for experience dropping

name: canEntityBeSeen
desc: returns true if the entity provided in the argument can be seen. (Raytrace)

name: canAttackClass
desc: Returns true if this entity can attack entities of the specified class.

name: getAIMoveSpeed
desc: the movespeed used for the new AI system

name: addPotionEffect
desc: adds a PotionEffect to the entity

name: heal
desc: Heal living entity (param: amount of half-hearts)

name: canDespawn
desc: Determines if an entity can be despawned, used on idle far away entities

name: getExperiencePoints
desc: Get the experience points the entity currently has.

name: getHeldItem
desc: Returns the item that this EntityLiving is holding, if any.

name: getEntityToAttack
desc: Returns current entities target

name: setPathToEntity
desc: sets the Entities walk path in EntityCreature

name: updateWanderPath
desc: Time remaining during which the Animal is sped up and flees.

name: isMovementCeased
desc: Disables a mob's ability to move on its own while true.

name: hasPath
desc: Returns true if entity has a path to follow

name: findPlayerToAttack
desc: Finds the closest player within 16 blocks to attack, or null if this Entity isn't interested in attacking (Animals, Spiders at day, peaceful PigZombies).

name: getBlockPathWeight
desc: Takes a coordinate in and returns a weight to determine how likely this creature will try to path to the block. Args: x, y, z

name: setTarget
desc: Sets the entity which is to be attacked.

name: attackEntity
desc: Basic mob attack. Default to touch of death in EntityCreature. Overridden by each mob to define their attack.

name: isCourseTraversable
desc: True if the ghast has an unobstructed line of travel to the waypoint.

name: canDamagePlayer
desc: Indicates weather the slime is able to damage the player (based upon the slime's size)

name: getSlimeParticle
desc: Returns the name of a particle effect that may be randomly created by EntitySlime.onUpdate()

name: getJumpSound
desc: Returns the name of the sound played when the slime jumps.

name: makesSoundOnLand
desc: Returns true if the slime makes a sound when it lands after a jump (based upon the slime's size)

name: getAttackStrength
desc: Gets the amount of damage dealt to the player when "attacked" by the slime.

name: getJumpDelay
desc: Gets the amount of time the slime needs to wait between jumps.

name: makesSoundOnJump
desc: Returns true if the slime makes a sound when it jumps (based upon the slime's size)

name: getSlimeSize
desc: Returns the size of the slime.

name: isValidLightLevel
desc: Checks to make sure the light is not too bright where the mob is spawning

name: teleportToEntity
desc: Teleport the enderman to another entity

name: setCarryingData
desc: Set the metadata of the block an enderman carries

name: setCarried
desc: Set the id of the block an enderman carries

name: teleportRandomly
desc: Teleport the enderman to a random nearby position

name: shouldAttackPlayer
desc: Checks to see if this enderman should be attacking this player

name: getCarried
desc: Get the id of the block an enderman carries

name: getCarryingData
desc: Get the metadata of the block an enderman carries

name: teleportTo
desc: Teleport the enderman

name: setCreeperState
desc: Sets the state of creeper, -1 to idle and 1 to be 'in fuse'

name: getPowered
desc: Returns true if the creeper is powered by a lightning bolt.

name: getCreeperFlashIntensity
desc: Params: (Float)Render tick. Returns the intensity of the creeper's flash when it is ignited.

name: getCreeperState
desc: Returns the current state of creeper, -1 is idle, 1 is 'in fuse'

name: becomeAngryAt
desc: Causes this PigZombie to become angry at the supplied Entity (which will be a player).

name: setBesideClimbableBlock
desc: Updates the WatchableObject (Byte) created in entityInit(), setting it to 0x01 if par1 is true or 0x00 if it is false.

name: spiderScaleAmount
desc: How large the spider should be scaled.

name: isBesideClimbableBlock
desc: Returns true if the WatchableObject (Byte) is 0x01 otherwise returns false. The WatchableObject is updated using setBesideClimableBlock.

name: setGrowingAge
desc: The age value may be negative or positive or zero. If it's negative, it get's incremented on each tick, if it's positive, it get's decremented each tick. With a negative value the Entity is considered a child.

name: getGrowingAge

If one value is valid and the other isn't, the valid value will be returned. Valid values are >= 0. Flow decay is the amount that a liquid has dissipated. 0 indicates a source block.
